    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So you're saying that things like education and self-regulation are sufficient alternatives to law. But don't you think that's a bit idealistic? Critics would say that relying on \"personal responsibility\" doesn't stop real-world harm like cybercrime or massive disinformation campaigns. Isn't it more practical to admit that some level of government oversight is objectively necessary for a functioning society?",
